{"NACARAT":[{"def":"A pale red color, with a cast of orange.","pos":""},{"def":"Fine linen or crape dyed of this color.","pos":""}],"NACELLE":[{"def":"The basket suspended from a balloon; hence, the framework forming the body of a dirigible balloon, and containing the machinery, passengers, etc.","pos":""}],"NACRE":[{"def":"A pearly substance which lines the interior of many shells, and is most perfect in the mother-of-pearl.","pos":""}],"NACREOUS":[{"def":"Consisting of, or resembling, nacre; pearly.","pos":""}]}